task.summary:
Initial Commit
Bootstraping using create-react-app Added CSS and Server support files

Building Book Component
Building the component tree Creating the book component to display a book and creating the pipeline of props and states to pass down the data for each book

Integrating getAll API call
Integrated the API to get data and display the books as per they shelf category

Functionality to update book category
Build function pipeline to pass new book category and id to update the bookshelf. Added attributes to select tag to track change

Functionality to update book category #2
Select's default value is the current shelf Books move and the shelves re-render to show change

Adding Routing
Added react router and search page

Search Page
Got books from API and displayed them as per user search. Edited the Books component to take shelf as a prop.

Search Page #2
Managed state of books. Now the books display the correct shelf. TODO: Check if re-rendering is required to update the shelf of the book as soon as it is changed to a new shelf. Can this be done within the book component without re-rendering the whole search page component

Final Commit #1
All app features work Used 'npm run build' to create a production version

Final Commit #2
Small adjustment to display name
